content:
The Case History related list on a case detail page tracks changes to the case. A new entry is added each time a user modifies a standard or custom field whose history is set to be tracked. Entries include the date, time, nature of the change, and who made the change.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To view cases: Read on cases

NOTE Changes to the Closed When Created field are only tracked when updated via the Lightning Platform API.
